      "content": "i mean u said \"critics argue\" but like, is there actual proof that these laws just make things worse? feels like some people just use the \"marginalized communities\" thing as an excuse to ignore the fact that crime needs to be punished to stop it. do the studies actually back up the idea that being tough on crime is a bad thing or is that just a political talking point?",
